invariant asyncio_extra115.TaskGroup_aexit_argc_4:
  description: "asyncio.TaskGroup.__aexit__.__code__.co_argcount == 4 — __aexit__ takes self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb (standard async context manager exit signature; 4 is the most co_argcount of any TaskGroup method); asyncio.TaskGroup.__aexit__.__qualname__=='TaskGroup.__aexit__' (len=19); asyncio.TaskGroup.__aexit__.__code__.co_qualname=='TaskGroup.__aexit__' (Python 3.11+); asyncio.TaskGroup.__aexit__.__code__.co_name=='__aexit__' (len=9); compare co_argcount: __init__==__aenter__==1 (minimum) < create_task==2 < __aexit__==4 (maximum); TaskGroup.__aexit__ handles exception propagation: it waits for all child tasks to finish, then if any raised exceptions, it raises an ExceptionGroup containing all of them; '__aexit__'=9 chars (method name len) ties with '__aenter__'=10... wait: '__aexit__'=9, '__aenter__'=10 (one char longer because 'enter' > 'exit' by 1); first standalone TaskGroup.__aexit__ argcount invariant; wave 255; verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  category: code_attrs
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: asyncio.TaskGroup.__aexit__.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__
  args: [4]
  expected: true

